from decimal import Decimal
from faker import Faker

def test_pydecimal_with_many_digits():
    fake = Faker()

    # Test with more than 15 digits
    decimal_value = fake.pydecimal(left_digits=16, right_digits=10)

    assert isinstance(decimal_value, Decimal)
    assert len(str(abs(int(decimal_value)))) <= 16  # Check left digit limit
    assert len(str(decimal_value).split('.')[1]) <= 10  # Check right digit limit

def test_pydecimal_positive_constraint():
    fake = Faker()

    # Test with positive flag
    decimal_value = fake.pydecimal(left_digits=5, right_digits=5, positive=True)

    assert decimal_value >= 0
    assert isinstance(decimal_value, Decimal)

def test_pydecimal_min_max_constraint():
    fake = Faker()

    # Test with min and max values
    decimal_value = fake.pydecimal(min_value=10, max_value=100, right_digits=2)

    assert 10 <= decimal_value <= 100
    assert isinstance(decimal_value, Decimal)
